[{"id":"f17d47f4fec7684f8517fe884bd8eff5","from":"Lesley Groff","from_email":"lesley@nysgllc.com","to":"J. Epstein","to_list":[{"name":"J. Epstein","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"FW: Boeing 727 paint","date":"2008-01-30T13:36:48.000Z","formatted_date":"Jan 30, 2008","formatted_time":"1:36 PM","body":"I have printed this out for you as well.\n\n \n\nFrom: LVJET@aol.com [mailto:LVJET@aol.com] \nSent: Wednesday, January 30, 2008 8:08 AM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nCc: Lesley Groff; JETCARE@aol.com\nSubject: Boeing 727 paint\n\n \n\nLeslely,\n\ncould you print this for Je to review,,,,it is a paint quote for the Boeing 727,,,,slot date is March 1st to start painting B727.\n\nthx,\n\nLarry v\n\n \n\nCustomer:   JEGE, Inc.                                                    Cust. Rep: Larry Morrison\n\nAddress     1514 Perimeter Road, Ste. 105A                   Phone: 561-317-3082\n\n                   West Palm Beach, FL  33406                         Reg #: N908JE                            \n\nAircraft Type: B727-100 Executive                                 TIMCO Sales Rep:  LCQ House\n\nQuote Expiration:  2/29/2008                                                                       \n\n\n\nGeneral Statement of Work:\n\nPerformance of paint services on aircraft N908JE as per Customer request.\n\n1.0      Fixed Pricing \n\n1.1      Strip and paint fuselage and vertical                                                      $106,200.00\n\n1.2      Sand and paint wings and horizontal from spar to spar             $12,700.00\n\n1.3      Polish leading edges                                                                               $4,200.00\n\n1.4      Sand and paint door surrounds                                                               $2,200.00\n\n1.5      Sand and paint wheel wells                                                                    $13,500.00\n\nTOTAL:                                                                                                          $138,800.00\n\nThe estimated span time to perform the services note above: 17 days\n\nLead time: 15 days for paint procurement\n\n     \n\n2.0      Pricing Detail:\n\n2.1       Strip and paint fuselage and vertical stabilizer.\n\n \n\n2.2       Scuff sand and paint wings and horizontal stabilizer from spar to spar.\n\n \n\n2.3       Sand and paint door surrounds.\n\n \n\n2.4       Sand and paint wheel wells.\n\n \n\n2.5       Any composite repairs will be accomplished on a time and material basis.\n\n \n\n2.6       Aircraft stripping is considered to be a single application of stripper to remove paint. Additional coats of stripper as required will be billed accordingly.\n\n            \n\n2.7       The final appearance of completed exterior decorative paint surfaces shall meet the following requirements when examined at 90- degrees from the painted surface and from the distance of 10 feet or more.\n\n \n\n\u00b7                     Exterior daylight examinations are limited to color match, skin quality polishing, and other workmanship defects not detected with artificial light sources.\n\n \n\n\u00b7                     The film shall be uniform in appearance and relatively free from sags, lint dirt, craters, orange peel, over spray, hazing and pigment float. In the case of rework within a color, it is acceptable to have a slight color variation if the rework does not detract from the overall appearance.\n\n \n\n\u00b7                     High solids nonmetallic \u201cmetallics\u201d have an increased tendency to orange peel. This increased orange peel is inherent to the materials and shall not be a cause for rejection.\n\n \n\n\u00b7                     All surface defects will be addressed and corrected prior to aircraft departure.\n\n \n\n \n\n2.8       TIMCO can provide certified, unbranded spot market Jet A fuel, upon request at TIMCO\u2019s price plus 10% handling and storage fee, plus an upload fee of $.30 per gallon.  If upload or download is required for performance of services, then customer shall pay fee of $.30 per gallon, but not the handling and storage, for the fuel uploaded and /or downloaded.\n\n\n\n\n\n________________________________\n\nStart the year off right. Easy ways to stay in shape <http://body.aol.com/fitness/winter-exercise?NCID=aolcmp00300000002489>  in the new year. \n\n","body_html":"<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" xmlns:dt=\"uuid:C2F41010-65B3-11d1-A29F-00AA00C14882\" xmlns:m=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40\"\nxmlns:ns0=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\">\n\n<head>\n<meta http-equiv=Content-Type content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\n<meta name=Generator content=\"Microsoft Word 12 (filtered medium)\">\n<!--[if !mso]>\n<style>\nv\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\no\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\nw\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\n.shape {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\n</style>\n<![endif]-->\n<style>\n<!--\n /* Font Definitions */\n @font-face\n\t{font-family:Calibri;\n\tpanose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4;}\n@font-face\n\t{font-family:Tahoma;\n\tpanose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\n /* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0in;\n\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\n\tfont-size:12.0pt;\n\tfont-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";}\na:link, span.MsoHyperlink\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\n\tcolor:blue;\n\ttext-decoration:underline;}\na:visited, span.MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\n\tcolor:purple;\n\ttext-decoration:underline;}\nspan.EmailStyle17\n\t{mso-style-type:personal-reply;\n\tfont-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\n\tcolor:#1F497D;}\n.MsoChpDefault\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\n\tfont-size:10.0pt;}\n@page Section1\n\t{size:8.5in 11.0in;\n\tmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;}\ndiv.Section1\n\t{page:Section1;}\n-->\n</style>\n<!--[if gte m